WEBVTT

00:02.959 --> 00:04.613
- ♪ Hey, here comes Sunny
keeping it fun ♪

00:04.743 --> 00:06.310
♪ Never says never,
never gives up ♪

00:06.441 --> 00:08.443
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:08.573 --> 00:10.140
♪ Hey

00:10.271 --> 00:11.968
♪ Gear up and go
in the Glam Van ♪

00:12.099 --> 00:13.709
♪ Hair styling
with her best friends ♪

00:13.839 --> 00:16.059
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:16.190 --> 00:19.193
♪ Oh, it's a Sunny Day

00:19.323 --> 00:21.499
♪ She'll put a smile
on your face ♪

00:21.630 --> 00:23.284
- Whoo-hoo!

00:23.414 --> 00:28.028
- ♪ Sunny is shining
all the way ♪

00:28.158 --> 00:31.074
♪ Yeah, she's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:31.205 --> 00:33.468
♪ Having a sunny, sunny day

00:33.598 --> 00:34.599
- Hoo-hoo!

00:42.912 --> 00:45.436
♪

00:45.567 --> 00:48.396
- Ugh. Why is this taking
so long?

00:48.526 --> 00:53.140
♪

00:53.270 --> 00:54.924
- Okay, Blair, ready to switch?

00:55.055 --> 00:57.405
- Ready, Sunny.

00:57.535 --> 00:59.755
- Going up.

00:59.885 --> 01:02.236
And going down.

01:02.366 --> 01:04.629
- Sunny, you're amazing.

01:04.760 --> 01:08.111
Oh, I don't know how you keep
all your customers straight.

01:08.242 --> 01:09.547
- Thanks, Cindy.

01:09.678 --> 01:11.723
But sometimes I keep
them curly.

01:11.854 --> 01:13.377
[giggles]Doodle.

01:13.508 --> 01:15.249
Will you fetch my spray bottle,
please?

01:15.379 --> 01:16.337
- Of course.

01:16.467 --> 01:17.729
I live for fetch.

01:17.860 --> 01:19.992
♪

01:20.123 --> 01:21.864
- And some coral nail polish?

01:21.994 --> 01:23.431
- Sure thing.

01:23.561 --> 01:25.389
♪

01:25.520 --> 01:27.652
Whoa.

01:27.783 --> 01:28.697
Oof.

01:28.827 --> 01:30.612
Whoa.

01:30.742 --> 01:32.396
I'm okay.

01:32.527 --> 01:34.224
Whoa.

01:34.355 --> 01:36.661
Whoa.

01:36.792 --> 01:38.315
- Bye. See you later.

01:38.446 --> 01:39.882
- Bye.
- Um.

01:40.012 --> 01:42.319
Could someone fetch me now?

01:42.450 --> 01:44.147
Whoa.
- [chuckles]

01:44.278 --> 01:46.584
We don't have time to fool
around today, Doodle.

01:46.715 --> 01:48.412
- Ah, whoa.

01:48.543 --> 01:50.240
- [laughs]

01:50.371 --> 01:52.764
- Ooh.
[sighs]

01:52.895 --> 01:56.028
Thanks, Rox.

01:56.159 --> 01:59.467
- I don't think the salon's
ever been this busy.

01:59.597 --> 02:01.338
- We are busy.

02:01.469 --> 02:04.994
We set a new record for most
appointments in one day.

02:05.125 --> 02:06.996
But we're almost finished.

02:07.127 --> 02:08.128
- There.

02:08.258 --> 02:09.781
You're all set.

02:09.912 --> 02:11.174
- Love it.

02:11.305 --> 02:12.784
- Ooh, wow.

02:12.915 --> 02:14.003
Thanks, Sunny.

02:14.134 --> 02:16.005
- Have a sunny day.

02:16.136 --> 02:17.441
- You're next, Jesse.

02:17.572 --> 02:20.792
♪

02:20.923 --> 02:22.359
- [groans]

02:22.490 --> 02:24.187
- Let's get to work.

02:27.016 --> 02:28.583
- How about that?

02:28.713 --> 02:30.672
- Whoa.

02:30.802 --> 02:34.110
- Who's next?

02:34.241 --> 02:36.025
- [groans]

02:36.156 --> 02:38.070
- Uh-huh. Yeah.

02:38.201 --> 02:40.247
Love these butterflies.

02:40.377 --> 02:44.512
♪

02:44.642 --> 02:45.904
- [giggles]

02:46.035 --> 02:47.819
[upbeat music]

02:47.950 --> 02:51.083
- There.
Looks great.

02:51.214 --> 02:52.998
- See ya.
- Thank you. Bye.

02:53.129 --> 02:55.131
- [giggles] Thanks for coming.
- [sighs]

02:55.262 --> 02:57.568
Just one more customer.
- Me!

02:57.699 --> 03:00.702
And it's two minutes past
my appointment time.

03:00.832 --> 03:03.574
- Outrageous.

03:03.705 --> 03:06.708
- Sorry, Lacey.

03:06.838 --> 03:08.492
So, how have you been?

03:08.623 --> 03:11.147
- In serious need
of a vacation,

03:11.278 --> 03:12.844
that's how.

03:12.975 --> 03:14.846
I've working so hard,

03:14.977 --> 03:16.065
right, KC?

03:16.196 --> 03:17.980
- Uh, yeah.

03:18.110 --> 03:20.417
Eating cupcakes and
listening to music

03:20.548 --> 03:23.551
can be really tiring.

03:23.681 --> 03:24.639
- The point is

03:24.769 --> 03:26.075
I'm headed to the beach,

03:26.206 --> 03:28.338
and I want an awesome
hairstyle.

03:28.469 --> 03:29.687
Something that says,

03:29.818 --> 03:32.212
"Here comes Lacey."

03:32.342 --> 03:34.214
- Nice of you to give people
a warning.

03:34.344 --> 03:35.954
- Doodle.
- I mean,

03:36.085 --> 03:37.869
beach hair sounds great.

03:38.000 --> 03:40.742
- Hmm. I think a mermaid braid
should do the trick.

03:40.872 --> 03:43.310
Blair, how about some music
to work to?

03:45.790 --> 03:47.444
- ♪ It's a Sunny celebration
- [gasps]

03:47.575 --> 03:48.880
The Surf Bros!

03:49.011 --> 03:50.839
[squeals]
- Is this their new song?

03:50.969 --> 03:52.623
It's so cool.

03:52.754 --> 03:54.930
- Yep, "Surfin' and Sunnin'."

03:55.060 --> 03:57.280
Rox, Blair, let's do this.

03:57.411 --> 04:00.327
- ♪ Yeah, we'll shimmy down
by the shore ♪

04:00.457 --> 04:04.374
♪ It's you, me, we're kicking
up a big beach party ♪

04:04.505 --> 04:08.987
♪ Dancing all the clouds
away ♪

04:09.118 --> 04:11.816
♪ We'll be surfin' and sunnin'
all day ♪

04:11.947 --> 04:16.734
♪ It's all you're bouncing
like a big beach ball ♪

04:16.865 --> 04:20.608
♪ Everybody, catch that wave

04:20.738 --> 04:23.524
♪ 'Cause we're surfin' and
sunnin' all day ♪

04:23.654 --> 04:26.657
♪ Surfin' and sunnin'
all day ♪

04:26.788 --> 04:29.617
♪ Surfin' and sunnin', yeah,
that's the way we play ♪

04:29.747 --> 04:31.096
♪ Whoo-hoo

04:31.227 --> 04:32.533
- [giggles]

04:32.663 --> 04:33.664
There.

04:33.795 --> 04:35.013
What do you think, Lacey?

04:35.144 --> 04:36.276
- Hm.

04:36.406 --> 04:37.494
Maybe.

04:37.625 --> 04:38.800
I'm not sure.

04:38.930 --> 04:41.629
KC, do you like it?

04:41.759 --> 04:43.370
- Whoa.

04:45.285 --> 04:48.592
Uh. Well. Uh--Hmm.
Maybe.

04:50.681 --> 04:53.336
- There. Now it looks good.

04:53.467 --> 04:56.339
- Exactly what I was going
to say.

04:56.470 --> 04:58.733
You've got the best style,
Lacey.

04:58.863 --> 05:01.388
- Glad you like it.
Have a sunny day.

05:01.518 --> 05:03.433
[door chimes jingle]

05:05.653 --> 05:06.958
[both sighing]

05:07.089 --> 05:08.569
- I'm exhausted.

05:08.699 --> 05:09.918
- Me too.

05:10.048 --> 05:12.616
- [yawns] Me three.

05:12.747 --> 05:14.749
[snoring]

05:14.879 --> 05:17.621
- We've definitely earned
a break.

05:17.752 --> 05:21.843
Hey, since Lacey was our last
customer for the day,

05:21.973 --> 05:24.933
why don't we follow
the Surf Bros' advice

05:25.063 --> 05:26.717
and head to the beach, too.

05:26.848 --> 05:28.502
both: Count us in.

05:28.632 --> 05:31.679
- There's just one thing we
need first.

05:31.809 --> 05:33.768
[together]
Beach makeovers!

05:33.898 --> 05:35.900
- Huh? Did I miss something?

05:36.031 --> 05:37.554
I feel like I missed something.

05:37.685 --> 05:39.121
Ooh, bone.

05:41.428 --> 05:42.907
- A little here.

05:43.038 --> 05:45.954
Mm, a little over here.

05:46.084 --> 05:48.522
Ooh, I like that.

05:48.652 --> 05:51.699
Over, under, over, under.

05:51.829 --> 05:53.527
♪

05:53.657 --> 05:54.963
Done.

05:55.093 --> 05:56.356
- Great, thanks!
- Wow.

05:56.486 --> 05:58.488
- My turn.

05:58.619 --> 06:01.491
[cheerful music]

06:01.622 --> 06:03.493
- Perfect.

06:03.624 --> 06:06.540
And we definitely need some
beach sunglasses.

06:06.670 --> 06:08.977
- [giggles]

06:09.107 --> 06:14.156
♪

06:14.286 --> 06:16.071
- I'm beach-ready.

06:16.201 --> 06:17.942
- [giggles] Beach braids.

06:18.073 --> 06:20.945
A summer look
for the Style Files.

06:22.556 --> 06:25.210
- Amazing hair.
Awesome clothes.

06:25.341 --> 06:27.604
I can't wait to hit the sand.

06:27.735 --> 06:30.781
- And I made a list of all the
activities we can do today.

06:30.912 --> 06:32.435
One, volleyball.

06:32.566 --> 06:33.871
Two, ice cream.

06:34.002 --> 06:35.090
Three--

06:35.220 --> 06:36.744
74, collect sea shells.

06:36.874 --> 06:38.528
75--
- Blair.

06:38.659 --> 06:41.270
Maybe you can read the rest
in the Glam Van.

06:41.401 --> 06:44.229
- Or it will be too late
to have a beach day.

06:44.360 --> 06:45.970
- [chuckles]
Sorry.

06:46.101 --> 06:47.929
I'm just so excited.

06:48.059 --> 06:49.887
- Ready, set...

06:50.018 --> 06:52.237
[together]
Gear up and go!

06:52.368 --> 06:59.462
♪

07:01.029 --> 07:03.292
[engine revving]

07:09.603 --> 07:11.779
- I haven't been to the beach
in forever.

07:11.909 --> 07:14.434
That's like seven forevers
in dog years.

07:14.564 --> 07:16.305
What do you think we
should do first?

07:16.436 --> 07:17.654
- Beach ball.

07:17.785 --> 07:19.264
- Really? I was thinking
more like

07:19.395 --> 07:21.397
a sandcastle or surfing--
- No.

07:21.528 --> 07:22.616
Beach ball, look!

07:22.746 --> 07:23.965
[all gasp]

07:25.445 --> 07:26.924
- Whoa.

07:27.055 --> 07:28.709
I don't remember the beach
being this dark.

07:28.839 --> 07:30.319
- Doodle.

07:33.235 --> 07:34.584
- Hi, everybody.

07:34.715 --> 07:36.151
Have you seen a beach ball?

07:36.281 --> 07:38.153
It's round and bouncy and--

07:38.283 --> 07:39.676
- Looks like this?

07:39.807 --> 07:42.287
- Yes, exactly like that.

07:42.418 --> 07:43.985
Have you seen it?

07:44.115 --> 07:46.204
- That is your beach ball,
Timmy.

07:46.335 --> 07:49.251
- Oh. Thanks, Sunny.

07:49.381 --> 07:51.079
Don't want to lose any
of these.

07:51.209 --> 07:53.864
You can't have a beach concert
without beach balls.

07:53.995 --> 07:57.781
Well, I guess you could, but it
wouldn't be as much fun.

07:57.912 --> 07:59.043
- Concert?

07:59.174 --> 08:00.741
What concert? And when?

08:00.871 --> 08:03.134
- In a couple of hours,
down by the boardwalk.

08:03.265 --> 08:05.006
The Surf Bros are playing;

08:05.136 --> 08:07.095
Sandy and Shell, see?

08:07.225 --> 08:10.794
- No way. As in the "Surfin'
and Sunnin'" Surf Bros?

08:10.925 --> 08:13.493
- We are their biggest fans.

08:13.623 --> 08:16.234
- Looks like we picked the
perfect day to go to the beach.

08:16.365 --> 08:19.847
- Now I'll have to change
our activities list,

08:19.977 --> 08:22.458
but it's so worth it.

08:22.589 --> 08:25.287
- I can save you all front row
spots if you like.

08:25.417 --> 08:27.419
- Thanks.
- Yay!

08:27.550 --> 08:30.074
- Now I just need to get these
beach balls to the stage.

08:30.205 --> 08:31.685
Oh, oopsies.

08:31.815 --> 08:33.643
Oh, whoa.

08:33.774 --> 08:35.297
Come back here.

08:35.427 --> 08:37.734
- Um, why don't we give
you a ride.

08:37.865 --> 08:40.041
♪

08:40.171 --> 08:44.001
- That's probably a good idea.

08:44.132 --> 08:46.787
- KC, quit squirming around.

08:46.917 --> 08:49.877
- Maybe we brought too much,
Lacey.

08:50.007 --> 08:51.922
I mean, snow shoes?

08:52.053 --> 08:53.358
On a beach?

08:53.489 --> 08:55.447
- They're tennis rackets, KC.

08:55.578 --> 08:57.319
[wind gusting]

08:57.449 --> 08:59.190
- [gasps]

09:00.452 --> 09:01.715
Our map.
- Aw.

09:01.845 --> 09:03.543
Sandy, I loved
that map.

09:03.673 --> 09:06.023
- Now how are we supposed to
find our way to the beach?

09:06.154 --> 09:08.809
- We could ask those guys.

09:08.939 --> 09:10.680
They seem nice.

09:10.811 --> 09:12.377
- Uh-huh, because they're us

09:12.508 --> 09:14.641
which means they're lost, too.

09:14.771 --> 09:17.774
- So, we're gonna be late
to our own concert?

09:17.905 --> 09:20.124
- Gee, Shell, I hadn't thoughtof that.

09:20.255 --> 09:21.561
Not awesome.

09:23.214 --> 09:25.913
[cheerful music]

09:26.043 --> 09:29.003
♪

09:29.133 --> 09:30.700
- Thanks again.

09:30.831 --> 09:32.702
And make sure you're back
in time for the concert.

09:32.833 --> 09:35.400
- We'll be there,
and in the meantime,

09:35.531 --> 09:37.402
we'll have time to do
everything else on our list.

09:37.533 --> 09:39.361
- Well, not everything.

09:39.491 --> 09:40.841
- Let's see.

09:40.971 --> 09:42.756
And the first thing
on the list is...

09:42.886 --> 09:45.149
have a beach party.

09:45.280 --> 09:47.064
[cheering]
- How low can you go?

09:47.195 --> 09:49.458
- Beach and party,

09:49.589 --> 09:51.547
two of my favorite words.

09:51.678 --> 09:53.680
- Come on.
- [giggles]

09:56.900 --> 09:58.728
- Sandy? Shell?

09:58.859 --> 10:00.425
Are you in there?

10:00.556 --> 10:03.341
Hm, where are those guys?

10:03.472 --> 10:06.083
- [groans]

10:06.214 --> 10:07.868
There. Comfy yet?

10:07.998 --> 10:11.219
- I can feel my paws now.
- Good enough.

10:11.349 --> 10:13.438
♪

10:13.569 --> 10:14.744
- Hm?

10:14.875 --> 10:16.398
Whoa.
- [gasps]

10:16.528 --> 10:18.922
But what--how?
[gasps]

10:19.053 --> 10:20.576
[wailing]

10:20.707 --> 10:22.230
Whoa.

10:22.360 --> 10:23.231
[grunts]

10:23.361 --> 10:24.754
Close that umbrella!

10:24.885 --> 10:26.147
- Can't close.

10:26.277 --> 10:27.931
Too--

10:32.109 --> 10:33.241
- Shell, look.

10:33.371 --> 10:35.025
A sign to the beach.

10:35.156 --> 10:39.551
- That way.
Concert, here we come.

10:39.682 --> 10:41.728
- Go, Rox!

10:41.858 --> 10:43.294
- Nice one, Blair.

10:43.425 --> 10:45.340
- Lower, please.

10:45.470 --> 10:47.211
[giggles]
- Oh, you can really bend.

10:47.342 --> 10:50.301
- Whoa, Sunny, how do you
do that?

10:50.432 --> 10:51.912
- Piece of cake. Watch me.

10:52.042 --> 10:54.262
Lower the bar,
Chihuahua height.

10:54.392 --> 10:57.004
I'm ready for a challenge.

10:57.134 --> 10:58.570
- You got it, Doodle!
- Whoo!

10:58.701 --> 11:00.834
[cheering]

11:00.964 --> 11:02.923
- Nice moves, Doodle.

11:03.053 --> 11:04.838
[cheering]

11:05.882 --> 11:07.318
- Balloon rides.

11:07.449 --> 11:09.016
Or ice cream.

11:09.146 --> 11:12.106
Or balloon rides and ice cream.

11:12.236 --> 11:13.107
Get them right here.

11:13.237 --> 11:14.761
- Hi, Johnny Ray,

11:14.891 --> 11:16.240
I don't suppose you've seen
the Surf Bros.

11:16.371 --> 11:19.026
- Lots of times.
I love their shows.

11:19.156 --> 11:20.897
- I mean have you seen
them today.

11:21.028 --> 11:23.421
- No, but I can't wait
for the concert,

11:23.552 --> 11:26.076
and--[gasps] they're not here
for the concert?

11:26.207 --> 11:28.775
- Shh.
No need for anyone to panic.

11:28.905 --> 11:30.472
Apart from me.

11:30.602 --> 11:32.648
I'm panicking quite a bit.

11:33.562 --> 11:34.998
- I don't know where we are,

11:35.129 --> 11:36.957
but I don't think
this is the beach.

11:37.087 --> 11:39.263
- And there's nobody
around to ask for directions.

11:39.394 --> 11:40.917
Where is everybody?

11:41.048 --> 11:42.571
Probably where we should be.

11:42.702 --> 11:44.181
At our concert.

11:44.312 --> 11:46.488
- [laughs]
We rule, bro.

11:46.618 --> 11:49.621
[sighs] Except at finding
our way to things.

11:49.752 --> 11:51.319
♪

11:51.449 --> 11:53.190
- Oh, Shell, this way.

11:53.321 --> 11:54.322
I see the sea.

11:54.452 --> 11:55.323
And where there's a sea,

11:55.453 --> 11:56.628
there's a beach.

11:56.759 --> 11:58.326
Awesome job, dude.

11:58.456 --> 12:00.284
[both gasp]

12:00.415 --> 12:01.808
- [sighs]

12:01.938 --> 12:04.027
The poster Surf Bros made it
to the beach.

12:04.158 --> 12:06.290
Why can't we?

12:07.465 --> 12:10.599
- [sighs] That limbo dancing
sure builds up an appetite.

12:10.730 --> 12:12.122
How's your ice cream, Doodle?

12:12.253 --> 12:15.125
- Can't talk--
[slurps] too happy.

12:15.256 --> 12:19.173
- Raspberry Ripple
on the boardwalk, done.

12:19.303 --> 12:21.001
[gasps] Thanks, Johnny Ray.

12:21.131 --> 12:22.785
- You're welcome--[gasps]

12:22.916 --> 12:25.092
- [chuffs]
- Suzanne.

12:25.222 --> 12:26.658
My hat.

12:26.789 --> 12:28.660
No, no, it's mine.

12:28.791 --> 12:30.053
[giggling]

12:30.184 --> 12:31.663
[gasping]

12:31.794 --> 12:33.796
[crowd chanting]
Surf Bros! Surf Bros!

12:33.927 --> 12:36.190
- Sounds like the show's
about to start.

12:36.320 --> 12:39.454
- We better get over there,
fast.

12:39.584 --> 12:41.586
- Concert or ice cream?

12:41.717 --> 12:43.588
Concert or ice cream?

12:43.719 --> 12:44.894
I got it!

12:45.025 --> 12:46.635
Concert and ice cream.

12:46.766 --> 12:48.768
Yeah.

12:50.204 --> 12:52.684
- How am I supposed to explain
to the crowd

12:52.815 --> 12:54.469
that the Surf Bros haven't
shown up.

12:54.599 --> 12:56.123
[sighs]
Oh--[clears throat]

12:56.253 --> 12:58.255
Hello, there.
Uh, the concert's not starting

12:58.386 --> 13:00.562
because, uh--
because...

13:00.692 --> 13:03.086
Because...

13:03.217 --> 13:04.305
- Hey, Timmy.
- [yelps]

13:04.435 --> 13:06.307
- Because what?

13:06.437 --> 13:08.831
Because the Surf Bros
aren't here.

13:08.962 --> 13:10.093
Oops.

13:10.224 --> 13:11.921
Did I say that out loud?

13:12.052 --> 13:13.096
- Oh, no.
- What?

13:13.227 --> 13:14.097
- Oh, dear.

13:14.228 --> 13:15.751
- [gasps]

13:15.882 --> 13:17.666
- But we can't have a beach
rock star concert

13:17.797 --> 13:20.103
without actual rock stars.

13:20.234 --> 13:21.365
- I know.

13:21.496 --> 13:22.453
I've looked everywhere,

13:22.584 --> 13:23.803
but they're not there

13:23.933 --> 13:25.152
which means they
should be here,

13:25.282 --> 13:26.196
but they're not.

13:26.327 --> 13:27.719
- [grunting]

13:27.850 --> 13:29.460
- When's this concert going
to start?

13:29.591 --> 13:31.898
We've been waiting and waiting
forever and ever.

13:32.028 --> 13:33.116
Right, KC?

13:33.247 --> 13:36.293
- About five minutes.

13:36.424 --> 13:38.165
[crowd chanting]
Surf Bros! Surf Bros!

13:38.295 --> 13:40.297
Surf Bros! Surf Bros!

13:40.428 --> 13:43.126
- This is a disaster.

13:45.520 --> 13:46.695
[crowd chanting]

13:46.826 --> 13:47.957
Surf Bros! Surf Bros!

13:48.088 --> 13:49.698
- Where are the Surf Bros,
Timmy?

13:49.829 --> 13:51.004
And when is our concert?

13:51.134 --> 13:53.920
- The concert isn't starting
yet, uh...

13:54.050 --> 13:55.573
Because--
- Um...

13:55.704 --> 13:57.706
Timmy's got a whole
warm-up show first.

13:57.837 --> 14:00.927
He brought a ton of beach balls
for the audience to play with.

14:01.057 --> 14:02.058
- I did?

14:02.189 --> 14:03.364
Oh, right.

14:03.494 --> 14:04.669
I did.

14:04.800 --> 14:06.193
- Here, Lacey.

14:06.323 --> 14:07.803
Why don't you get the first
one going?

14:07.934 --> 14:10.197
- Ooh, this means we'll be

14:10.327 --> 14:12.634
part of the Surf Bros show.

14:12.764 --> 14:16.159
- And now you throw the ball
out to the crowd, Lacey.

14:16.290 --> 14:18.770
- But it's my ball now.

14:18.901 --> 14:20.947
[groans]
Okay.

14:21.077 --> 14:23.123
- Over here, Lacey.
- Yeah!

14:23.253 --> 14:26.082
[cheering]
- Beach balls!

14:26.213 --> 14:28.215
- Well, that should keep them
busy for about...

14:28.345 --> 14:30.260
oh, 12 minutes.

14:30.391 --> 14:33.437
- We'll never find
the Surf Bros in 12 minutes.

14:33.568 --> 14:35.222
- Never say never.

14:35.352 --> 14:36.310
- Sunny's right.

14:36.440 --> 14:37.789
I'm being supportive.

14:37.920 --> 14:39.095
I don't think we'll find
them in time.

14:39.226 --> 14:40.792
- When things look bad,

14:40.923 --> 14:43.143
you just have to change
your point of view.

14:43.273 --> 14:44.753
And up in the balloon,

14:44.884 --> 14:47.147
we'll be able to view
the whole town.

14:47.277 --> 14:49.584
- Good idea.
- That should do it.

14:49.714 --> 14:51.716
- You three keep
the audience entertained

14:51.847 --> 14:53.762
until Doodle and I get back.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.416
- Huh? Wait, wait, wait.

14:55.546 --> 14:56.852
I'm going up in that thing?

14:56.983 --> 14:58.158
- We are.

14:58.288 --> 15:00.725
[cheerful music]

15:00.856 --> 15:03.206
I just need to get one thing.

15:11.127 --> 15:12.824
You should take a look, Doodle.

15:12.955 --> 15:14.783
It's a great view.

15:14.914 --> 15:16.219
- [whimpering]

15:16.350 --> 15:18.004
Whoa.

15:18.134 --> 15:20.963
Everything is as tiny as my dog
kibble from up here.

15:21.094 --> 15:23.618
Hey, I can see the salon.

15:23.748 --> 15:26.751
- And there's the bakery.

15:26.882 --> 15:28.579
[gasps]
And look.

15:28.710 --> 15:30.451
All that green is the park.

15:30.581 --> 15:33.106
- We can see everything
from up here.

15:33.236 --> 15:36.805
Well, everything except
the Surf Bros.

15:36.936 --> 15:38.676
- Hm.

15:38.807 --> 15:40.940
I think we'll need to take a
closer look for that.

15:41.070 --> 15:44.204
Good thing I brought
my Glam-a-go-go.

15:44.334 --> 15:46.467
Some hair curlers,

15:46.597 --> 15:48.860
a few bobby pins.

15:48.991 --> 15:50.601
- I have no idea what
you're making,

15:50.732 --> 15:52.255
but I know it's going
to be good.

15:52.386 --> 15:55.171
- Oh, and a couple
of magnifying lenses.

15:55.302 --> 15:58.827
[upbeat music]

15:58.958 --> 16:01.090
- [gasps] It's a telescope.

16:01.221 --> 16:04.659
- Yep, let's hope it helps us
find what we're looking for.

16:09.490 --> 16:12.101
- Okay, I am done
with the beach balls.

16:12.232 --> 16:13.798
We want the Surf Bros!

16:13.929 --> 16:15.104
all: Yeah!

16:15.235 --> 16:16.714
- They'll be here soon.

16:16.845 --> 16:18.151
But, um, first...

16:18.281 --> 16:20.631
I'd like to juggle for you.

16:20.762 --> 16:25.114
- Whoa-ho-ho.
Oh, oh. Whoa.

16:25.245 --> 16:27.682
- Bring out the Surf Bros!

16:27.812 --> 16:30.119
Yeah!

16:30.250 --> 16:31.555
- [sighs] That's all I got.

16:31.686 --> 16:33.209
Your turn.

16:33.340 --> 16:37.735
- Mm. I really hope Sunny gets
back soon.

16:37.866 --> 16:41.217
[upbeat music]

16:43.611 --> 16:44.786
- There they are!

16:44.916 --> 16:46.353
Doodle, take us down.

16:46.483 --> 16:48.572
- Aye, aye, Air Captain Sunny.

16:48.703 --> 16:51.184
♪

16:51.314 --> 16:52.881
- Ahoy, there!

16:53.012 --> 16:54.448
Need a lift?
- Huh?

16:54.578 --> 16:57.277
- Up here!
- What?

16:57.407 --> 16:59.148
both: Whoa.

16:59.279 --> 17:01.933
- I'm Sunny, and this is
Doodle.

17:02.064 --> 17:03.848
- Hey, Doodle.
I'm Sandy.

17:03.979 --> 17:05.415
- And I'm Shell.

17:05.546 --> 17:06.851
And together we're...

17:06.982 --> 17:08.462
[together]
The Surf Bros.

17:08.592 --> 17:10.812
- We know! You're my
biggest fan.

17:10.942 --> 17:12.944
I mean I'm your biggest fan.

17:13.075 --> 17:15.034
Hi, I'm Doodle.

17:15.164 --> 17:17.514
- We're here to take
to your concert.

17:17.645 --> 17:18.950
- You know where the beach is?

17:19.081 --> 17:20.561
Impressive.

17:20.691 --> 17:22.345
We've had no luck.

17:22.476 --> 17:24.391
- Only problem is

17:24.521 --> 17:26.784
there's no room for us to land
down there.

17:26.915 --> 17:29.048
So you'll have to grab
onto this.

17:29.178 --> 17:31.006
♪

17:31.137 --> 17:32.355
- Whoa.

17:32.486 --> 17:34.618
Whoa!

17:34.749 --> 17:36.359
- Oh, gotcha.

17:36.490 --> 17:38.361
That rope's way too slippery.

17:38.492 --> 17:40.929
We'll never be able to hang on.

17:41.060 --> 17:45.064
- There has be some way to make
it easier for them to climb up.

17:45.194 --> 17:46.848
Too bad it's rope and not hair

17:46.978 --> 17:48.415
or you'd know what to do.

17:48.545 --> 17:50.765
That's it! Well done, Doodle.

17:50.895 --> 17:52.245
- You're welcome?

17:52.375 --> 17:54.682
- I'm giving this rope
a make-over.

17:54.812 --> 17:57.424
Some weaving should do
the trick.

17:57.554 --> 18:00.427
♪

18:00.557 --> 18:01.906
- Hm?

18:02.037 --> 18:04.518
♪

18:04.648 --> 18:07.129
Whoa.

18:07.260 --> 18:09.044
- There.

18:09.175 --> 18:10.741
- Sweet.

18:10.872 --> 18:13.657
Things are totally looking up.

18:13.788 --> 18:18.619
[both grunting]

18:18.749 --> 18:22.753
- Ooh, ha, yeah.
- [yodeling]

18:22.884 --> 18:23.972
- Oh, yeah.

18:24.103 --> 18:26.670
- Let's hear it
for Rox and Blair.

18:26.801 --> 18:30.500
- Let's hear it for, "When are
the Surf Bros gonna start?"

18:30.631 --> 18:32.807
[crowd chanting]
We want the Surf Bros!

18:32.937 --> 18:35.331
We want the Surf Bros!

18:35.462 --> 18:37.638
- [whimpering]

18:37.768 --> 18:39.205
- It's not every day we share
a hot air balloon

18:39.335 --> 18:40.597
with rock stars.

18:40.728 --> 18:42.599
I'm so glad we found you two.

18:42.730 --> 18:44.427
- We're glad we found you.

18:44.558 --> 18:46.212
We'd hate to miss our own show.

18:46.342 --> 18:48.649
- Did I mention I have
experience singing backup?

18:48.779 --> 18:50.651
Just so you know,
I'm available.

18:50.781 --> 18:52.043
- Whoa.

18:52.174 --> 18:53.697
Whoa.
What was that?

18:53.828 --> 18:54.829
- The balloon.

18:54.959 --> 18:56.439
We're sinking.

18:56.570 --> 18:57.701
[dramatic music]

18:57.832 --> 18:59.312
It's running out of hot air.

18:59.442 --> 19:00.965
- But we're not
at the beach yet.

19:01.096 --> 19:04.186
- Wait, I think I have
something that can help.

19:04.317 --> 19:07.407
[upbeat music]

19:07.537 --> 19:09.017
Hot air to-go.

19:09.148 --> 19:09.887
[hair dryer whirring]

19:10.018 --> 19:12.063
- Whoa. Awesome.

19:12.194 --> 19:14.544
♪

19:14.675 --> 19:16.329
Expert dryer moves.

19:16.459 --> 19:17.286
- And look.

19:17.417 --> 19:19.245
I see the concert.

19:19.375 --> 19:21.334
crowd:
Surf Bros! Surf Bros!

19:21.464 --> 19:23.074
Surf Bros!

19:23.205 --> 19:25.816
- [sighs] I guess I'll have
to break the news.

19:25.947 --> 19:28.036
[gulps]
Um...

19:28.167 --> 19:29.603
Ladies and gentlemen,

19:29.733 --> 19:32.127
I'm sorry to say that
the Surf Bros are--

19:32.258 --> 19:34.608
- Right there!Look!

19:34.738 --> 19:38.220
[all cheering]
- There they are!

19:39.787 --> 19:41.658
- As I was about to say,

19:41.789 --> 19:44.966
the Surf Bros are in the house!

19:45.096 --> 19:47.751
Well, on the beach!

19:47.882 --> 19:49.971
[cheering]

19:50.101 --> 19:51.842
- Hello, Friendly Falls.

19:51.973 --> 19:53.322
Anybody order a large concert

19:53.453 --> 19:55.281
with a side of awesome?

19:55.411 --> 19:56.630
- We figured we'd just drop in.

19:56.760 --> 20:00.329
[cheers and applause]

20:00.460 --> 20:01.983
- You did it!
- Yay!

20:02.113 --> 20:04.768
Never make me yodel again.

20:04.899 --> 20:07.162
- We're gonna kick things off
with our latest hit song,

20:07.293 --> 20:08.642
"Surfin' and Sunnin'"

20:08.772 --> 20:10.426
[cheers and applause]

20:10.557 --> 20:12.733
- But we wouldn't be here
to sing our song

20:12.863 --> 20:15.692
or even have a concert
without a special someone.

20:15.823 --> 20:17.477
Sunny!

20:17.607 --> 20:18.956
- So we're dedicating this song
to her!

20:19.087 --> 20:20.915
- [gasps]
Me?

20:21.045 --> 20:22.395
This is so cool.

20:22.525 --> 20:24.135
- [scoffs] I could have
flown in a balloon

20:24.266 --> 20:26.007
if someone asked me to.

20:26.137 --> 20:27.661
- Still want to sing backup?

20:27.791 --> 20:29.793
- Are chew toys squeaky?

20:29.924 --> 20:31.186
That's a yes!

20:31.317 --> 20:33.319
- You too, Sunny.
Come on up.

20:33.449 --> 20:37.279
[cheers and applause]

20:37.410 --> 20:39.673
♪ It's a sunny celebration

20:39.803 --> 20:42.371
- ♪ Fire up the summer song

20:42.502 --> 20:45.200
♪ Cares are in my rear view

20:45.331 --> 20:48.377
both: ♪ Want to hit the surf
with you ♪

20:48.508 --> 20:51.815
♪ Yeah, we'll shimmy down
by the shore ♪

20:51.946 --> 20:56.385
♪ It's you, me, kicking up a
big beach party ♪

20:56.516 --> 21:00.650
♪ Dancing all the clouds away

21:00.781 --> 21:03.479
♪ We'll be surfin' and sunnin'
all day ♪

21:03.610 --> 21:08.223
♪ It's all you're bouncing like
a big beach ball ♪

21:08.354 --> 21:11.966
♪ Everybody catch that wave

21:12.096 --> 21:15.274
♪ 'Cause we're surfin' and
sunnin' all day ♪

21:15.404 --> 21:18.364
♪ Surfin' and sunnin' all day

21:18.494 --> 21:21.671
♪ Surfin' and sunnin', yeah,
that's the way we play ♪

21:21.802 --> 21:25.371
[cheers and applause]

21:25.501 --> 21:27.111
- Awesome concert.

21:27.242 --> 21:28.896
- Amazing.

21:29.026 --> 21:31.986
- Yep! Now, that's how you do a
day at the beach.

21:32.116 --> 21:33.204
[laughing]

21:33.335 --> 21:35.250
both: One more time!

21:35.381 --> 21:39.602
all: ♪ It's you, me, kicking up
a big beach party ♪

21:39.733 --> 21:40.777
♪ Dancing all

21:42.692 --> 21:44.172
- Hi, it's me, Sunny,

21:44.303 --> 21:46.435
with another look
inside the Style Files.

21:46.566 --> 21:49.699
What a beautiful
mermaid braid.

21:49.830 --> 21:51.571
Gorgeous.

21:51.701 --> 21:53.137
For this hairstyle and more,

21:53.268 --> 21:55.009
check out Sunny Style Files

21:55.139 --> 21:57.620
at nickjr.com and
the Nick Jr. app.

21:57.751 --> 21:59.883
Keep smiling, keep styling.

22:00.014 --> 22:01.189
[laughs]

22:05.628 --> 22:08.457
[upbeat music]

22:08.588 --> 22:15.638
♪
